# Technical decisions (cross-REN knowledge)

Reusable technical lessons accumulated across RENs. Each entry is short, general, and applies beyond the REN where it was first observed.

Contrast with `ren/REN_<N>/decisions.md`: that file holds REN-specific choices ("for this REN I chose subquery because the user X asked Y"). This file holds patterns that apply everywhere ("NPS 11.x syntax quirk Z", "BGE-M3 chunk size sweet spot").

## Format

Each entry has:

- A short title.
- Date first observed.
- Context (1-2 lines).
- Decision / pattern (what we do).
- Applies to (when this lesson is relevant).

